♪ Enough. ♪

651
00:37:26,911 --> 00:37:30,129
How do you feel?

652
00:37:31,817 --> 00:37:35,368
Like I was just born.

653
00:37:35,403 --> 00:37:38,888
Like I'm the luckiest
person in the world.

654
00:37:38,924 --> 00:37:42,392
It's never been like this, ever,

655
00:37:42,427 --> 00:37:45,028
just breathing.

656
00:37:47,132 --> 00:37:48,881
My parents?

657
00:37:48,916 --> 00:37:50,433
Hey, Elo.

658
00:37:50,468 --> 00:37:52,246
Your dad's procedure went great.

659
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:55,088
Your mom...

660
00:37:55,123 --> 00:37:58,091
There were some complications
with the pulmonary artery.

661
00:37:58,126 --> 00:38:01,127
It can happen in
difficult surgeries like this.

662
00:38:01,163 --> 00:38:04,080
- Recovery's not gonna be easy.
- But...

663
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:05,849
we believe she can make it.

664
00:38:05,884 --> 00:38:08,935
Oh... Mom.

665
00:38:20,132 --> 00:38:22,098
Mom, I'm here.

666
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:27,137
Right here, where you've
always been: beside me,

667
00:38:27,172 --> 00:38:30,923
helping me.

668
00:38:30,959 --> 00:38:33,193
Mom, can you hear me?

669
00:38:50,144 --> 00:38:52,111
You're famous.

670
00:38:52,146 --> 00:38:54,480
Just think how much
more insufferable you'll be.

671
00:38:54,516 --> 00:38:55,981
I wouldn't count on it.

672
00:38:56,017 --> 00:38:58,151
I have recently
dined on humble pie,

673
00:38:58,186 --> 00:39:00,453
and it's a flavor I
will not soon forget.

674
00:39:00,488 --> 00:39:03,022
That surgery was insane.

675
00:39:03,057 --> 00:39:05,052
I mean, we're all
proud of the work we did

676
00:39:05,076 --> 00:39:06,854
and are happy for
Eloise and her family,

677
00:39:06,878 --> 00:39:09,212
but that could have
ended very badly.

678
00:39:09,247 --> 00:39:11,030
A triple tragedy.

679
00:39:11,066 --> 00:39:14,016
Skill certainly played a
large part, but so did luck.

680
00:39:14,051 --> 00:39:17,136
It was practically a miracle.

681
00:39:17,172 --> 00:39:20,056
Check it out. Our next surgery.

682
00:39:20,092 --> 00:39:22,358
What are you gonna do?

683
00:39:22,393 --> 00:39:24,894
Uh,<i> we</i> are going
to perform a flawless

684
00:39:24,929 --> 00:39:27,030
aortic valve replacement.

685
00:39:27,065 --> 00:39:29,915
- With a QuoVadis valve?
- A-A QuoVadis valve? Excuse me?

686
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:32,668
There are no QuoVadis
valves on Chastain shelves.

687
00:39:32,703 --> 00:39:34,565
Are you telling me...

688
00:39:34,589 --> 00:39:36,050
Bell pulled them?

689
00:39:36,074 --> 00:39:38,057
Every last one.

690
00:39:38,092 --> 00:39:41,060
We've got the old reliable
valves back for good.

691
00:39:41,095 --> 00:39:42,790
- Well, today is
truly miraculous.
- Mm.

692
00:39:42,814 --> 00:39:46,232
Bell, of all people,
did the right thing.

693
00:39:50,055 --> 00:39:53,022
You pulled the
valves. Are you insane?

694
00:39:53,058 --> 00:39:55,107
It was the right thing to do.

695
00:39:55,142 --> 00:39:58,744
And I believe, eventually,
you'll agree with my decision.

696
00:39:58,797 --> 00:40:00,563
This is way out of line.

697
00:40:00,598 --> 00:40:02,781
Obviously, there will
be consequences.

698
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:04,817
You'll regret this, Dr. Bell.

699
00:40:13,461 --> 00:40:16,012
Long day.

700
00:40:18,799 --> 00:40:21,033
A great day.

701
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:24,432
I'm leaving, Dr. B. Uh, don't
forget you have that dinner

702
00:40:24,456 --> 00:40:26,467
with the CEO of
Atlanta General at 8:00.

703
00:40:26,491 --> 00:40:28,874
I canceled it. I have surgery.

704
00:40:28,909 --> 00:40:30,655
Ah, that's a nice change.

705
00:40:30,679 --> 00:40:33,362
See you tomorrow, boss.

706
00:40:36,585 --> 00:40:38,651
To you.

707
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:42,454
Thank you for what you did.

708
00:40:45,043 --> 00:40:48,010
Thank you.

709
00:40:48,046 --> 00:40:50,029
Allow me.

710
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:05,111
It's a good look.

711
00:41:05,146 --> 00:41:08,514
Yeah, I just had it pressed.

712
00:41:15,173 --> 00:41:17,100
You've reached Mark Truscott,

713
00:41:17,124 --> 00:41:19,284
Director of the Center
of Devices at the FDA.

714
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:21,110
Leave a message.

715
00:41:28,153 --> 00:41:30,703
<i>You broke into Julian's place?</i>

716
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:32,388
Not exactly.

717
00:41:32,423 --> 00:41:34,874
The landlady let me
in to get Julian's cat.

718
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,626
Don't ask.

719
00:41:36,661 --> 00:41:39,711
- And you just took
her phone bill.
- Yes.

720
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:42,014
Look at the last number
that Julian called.

721
00:41:42,049 --> 00:41:45,168
On the 3rd, the day
I saw her in the park.

722
00:41:45,203 --> 00:41:46,719
The day she disappeared.

723
00:41:46,755 --> 00:41:48,715
I tried the number
about an hour ago

724
00:41:48,739 --> 00:41:51,302
and I got an answering machine.

725
00:41:51,326 --> 00:41:54,477
It was an office at the FDA.

726
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:56,345
Julian was a device rep.

727
00:41:56,381 --> 00:41:57,925
She probably called
them all the time.

728
00:41:57,949 --> 00:41:59,227
Or maybe she found something out

729
00:41:59,251 --> 00:42:01,384
and she was trying
to blow the whistle.

730
00:42:03,204 --> 00:42:06,706
Look, you said it yourself.

731
00:42:06,741 --> 00:42:09,759
Bradley died because
of a defective valve.

732
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:13,679
He was my best friend.

733
00:42:13,715 --> 00:42:17,083
Did QuoVadis know
the valve was bad?

734
00:42:17,118 --> 00:42:21,387
If so, they killed him.

735
00:42:21,423 --> 00:42:24,173
Julian told me that
something was wrong at work.

736
00:42:24,209 --> 00:42:27,993
She felt like everything
was falling apart.

737
00:42:28,029 --> 00:42:29,879
What do you think she meant?

738
00:42:31,198 --> 00:42:33,716
I think she was in danger.

739
00:42:33,751 --> 00:42:37,219
Did they kill her?
Did she run away?

740
00:42:37,254 --> 00:42:39,906
I don't know.

741
00:42:39,941 --> 00:42:42,892
Something is up with QuoVadis.

742
00:42:48,466 --> 00:42:50,999
Let's figure out
what to do next.

